{
  "stem": "2578.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "When they got through with this quarter, they told the remaining Jews to go back to their houses and stay there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they moved to the next block of houses, or to the next street.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And this went on, from block to block, for eight days.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And instead of 5,000 or 10,000 that they originally asked for, they picked up, if I remember correctly, about 15,000 Jews.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "15,000.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was the worst and the biggest [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] evacuation of Jews from the ghetto into-- and at that time they were sent-- we-- we found out later that they were-- they were sent to Auschwitz, to the crematorias.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Again, rumors came in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because it was-- it was a time that-- you see, what we found out was that when the Jews came into Auschwitz, the clothes were taken off from them, and they were sent to the crematorias.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At certain-- at certain times, the clothes were sent back to the Lodz ghetto for cleaning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And people started to recognize certain pieces-- certain articles of clothing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they knew that something was wrong, because there was no reason for them to-- to get-- to get back or to see these pieces of clothing.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they recognized, and they understood that something happened to them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then, again, more and more-- when the extermination of the Jews began to be spread out, in the-- in '42 and '43, more and more ideas and more and more news came in, into the ghetto, about things that [INAUDIBLE] there are such things like concentration camps and labor camps and-- and extermination camps.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Gas chambers and crematorias and so on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But there was very little we could-- we could do about it.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
